parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key is stuck in the ignition
the vehicle won't start
the security light blinks
and the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The hazard lights
headlights
radio
windows
and heater/AC malfunction
the dash lights flicker
and the security light blinks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The security light blinks
the vehicle won't start
and the key needs to be reset.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The exhaust leak
the vehicle stalls
and the exhaust system rusts out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle vibrates when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Hazard Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal and hazard light system can cause accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, leading to potential crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The turn signals and hazard lights may work intermittently
fail to illuminate
or produce a clicking or ticking noise. The hazard lights may remain illuminated even when not in use. The turn signals may only work when the hazard lights are activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling lines can cause coolant to leak, leading to overheating of the engine and transmission, which can result in engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
white smoke
overheating of the engine and transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
fails to return to the idle position
or accelerates the vehicle without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can prevent airbags from deploying in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: None reported in these complaints
but the issue is mentioned as a concern in complaint 10633122.
